# Tessera Front Desk — environment template.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in a key. NEVER commit `.env.local`.
# The app and eval both run at $0: the primary path is Google AI Studio's free tier.

# --- LLM provider (pick ONE; Gemini is the primary, free path) ----------------

# 1. PRIMARY — Google AI Studio, native @ai-sdk/google provider.
#    gemini-2.5-flash is on the free tier (~10 requests/min at time of writing),
#    which is why the app and the multi-turn eval both cost $0.
#    Get a key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# 2. FALLBACK — Groq (OpenAI-compatible endpoint), llama-3.3-70b-versatile.
#    Only used when GEMINI_API_KEY is absent. Also a free tier.
#    Get a key: https://console.groq.com/keys
# GROQ_API_KEY=

# --- Database (optional) ------------------------------------------------------
# Local dev needs NOTHING here: the app defaults to a local SQLite file
# (`file:local.db`) created by `npm run seed`. For a hosted Turso database in
# production, set both of these and the same code talks to Turso over the wire.
# TURSO_DATABASE_URL=
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=

# --- Abuse guard (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Turnstile is fully env-gated: leave unset to disable it entirely.
# When set, the client must attach a token that the server verifies.
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=
